---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Support"
  description="Get help with Fierro. Find answers to common questions, contact our support team, or manage your account and subscription."
  ogImage="/og/support.png"
>
  <!-- Lightweight dark header band -->
  <section class="bg-gunmetal pt-28 pb-10">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-off-white">Support</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-off-white/60">We're here to help</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Support content -->
  <section class="bg-off-white py-12 lg:py-16">
    <article class="prose-legal mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        Have a question, found a bug, or need help with your account? Reach out
        and we'll get back to you as soon as possible.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Email:</strong>
        <a href="mailto:support@getfierro.com">support@getfierro.com</a>
      </p>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>Getting Started</h3>

      <h4>How do I create an account?</h4>
      <p>
        Download Fierro from the App Store or visit
        <a href="https://app.getfierro.com/signup">app.getfierro.com/signup</a>
        to create a free account. You can sign up with your email or use Google
        or Apple sign-in.
      </p>

      <h4>Is Fierro free to use?</h4>
      <p>
        Yes. The Home plan is free forever and includes one active project, basic
        expense tracking, and email support. Paid plans unlock more projects,
        advanced features, and priority support. See our
        <a href="/pricing">pricing page</a> for details.
      </p>

      <h3>Account &amp; Billing</h3>

      <h4>How do I manage my subscription?</h4>
      <p>
        If you subscribed through the App Store, manage your subscription in your
        device's Settings &gt; Apple&nbsp;ID &gt; Subscriptions. For
        subscriptions purchased on the web, go to your account settings at
        <a href="https://app.getfierro.com">app.getfierro.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h4>How do I cancel my subscription?</h4>
      <p>
        You can cancel anytime. App Store subscriptions are cancelled through
        your device settings. Web subscriptions can be cancelled from your Fierro
        account settings. You'll retain access until the end of your current
        billing period.
      </p>

      <h4>How do I request a refund?</h4>
      <p>
        Refunds for App Store purchases are handled by Apple. Visit
        <a href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com">reportaproblem.apple.com</a>
        to request a refund. For web purchases, email us at
        <a href="mailto:support@getfierro.com">support@getfierro.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h4>How do I delete my account?</h4>
      <p>
        To request account deletion, email
        <a href="mailto:support@getfierro.com">support@getfierro.com</a> from
        the email address associated with your account. We will process your
        request and delete your data in accordance with our
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>Using Fierro</h3>

      <h4>What platforms is Fierro available on?</h4>
      <p>
        Fierro is available as an iOS app and a web dashboard at
        <a href="https://app.getfierro.com">app.getfierro.com</a>. Your data
        syncs across both platforms in real time.
      </p>

      <h4>Can I share a project with my contractor or team?</h4>
      <p>
        Yes. On the Plus plan and above you can invite team members to
        collaborate on projects with role-based permissions. Each collaborator
        needs their own Fierro account.
      </p>

      <h4>How do I export my data?</h4>
      <p>
        You can request a full export of your project data by emailing
        <a href="mailto:support@getfierro.com">support@getfierro.com</a>. We'll
        provide your data in a portable format.
      </p>

      <h2>Policies</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
